## Fraud Type Descriptions (for page subtitles)

| Tab | Description |
|---|---|
| **APP Fraud** | Victims manipulated into authorising push payments to fraudster-controlled accounts |
| **Unauthorised Fraud** | Transactions executed without the account holder's knowledge or consent (account takeover, credential theft) |
| **First-Party Fraud** | Account holders making legitimate purchases then falsely claiming fraud for refunds |
| **Collusion Fraud** | Coordinated fraud rings with multiple accounts working together to exploit PayPal systems |

